angel /ˈeɪndʒəl/

(angels) 

1. N-COUNT Angels are spiritual beings that some people believe are God's servants in heaven. 天使 

例： The artist usually painted his angels with multi-coloured wings. 这位艺术家通常给他的天使画上多彩的翅膀。 

2. N-COUNT You can call someone you like very much an angel in order to show affection, especially when they have been kind to you or done you a favour. 天使 [情感] 

例： Thank you a thousand times, you're an angel. 千恩万谢了，你是个天使。 

3. N-COUNT If you describe someone as an angel , you mean that they seem to be very kind and good. 大好人 [表赞许] 

例： Papa thought her an angel. 爸爸认为她是个大好人。

